<TEXT>
here is a list of some major us mine disasters 
dec 19 1984 faulty air compressor starts underground fire 
that kills 27 coal miners at the wilberg mine near orangeville utah 
march 911 1976 fifteen miners and 11 rescuers die as two 
methane gas explosions shake mine in oven fork ky 
may 3 1972 fire fills the sunshine mine in kellogg idaho 
with smoke and poisonous gas killing 91 miners two people survived 
the fire in the nations richest and deepest silver mine living for 
a week 4800 feet below the surface by eating the lunches of their 
fallen comrades and tapping water from pipes 
dec 30 1970 mine disaster in hyden ky kills 38 miners 
nov 20 1968 explosions and fire at consolidated coals no 9 
mine in farmington wva kill 78 people twenty major explosions 
and many more minor ones rocked the mines 100 miles of tunnels for 
nine days this disaster led to the landmark federal coal mine 
health and safety act passed by congress in 1969 
dec 21 1951 west frankfort ill mine disaster kills 119 
people 
march 25 1947 mine disaster in centralia ill kills 111 coal 
miners 
may 19 1928 coal mine disaster in mather pa kills 195 
feb 28 1923 second major mine disaster within 10 years in 
dawson nm kills 120 people 
oct 22 1913 mine explosion in dawson nm kills 263 people 
nov 13 1909 mine explodes at cherry ill killing 259 
dec 19 1907 explosion at jacobs creek pa kills 239 people 
dec 6 1907 in the nations worst mine disaster 361 to 370 
miners are killed as electrical sparks apparently ignite an 
explosion in a network of coal mines at monongah wva 
may 1 1900 premature blasting powder explosion kills 200 
people at scofield utah 
 
</TEXT>
