<TEXT>
people whove been wronged by a boss 
jilted by a lover or otherwise insulted are finding the ultimate 
revenge has just plopped in their laps 
a new company catering to the revengeminded will send a genuine 
cow pie nestled in an 8inch pie tin wrapped in plastic and boxed 
like baked goods for 1695 or 995 on special fake flies are 
75 cents extra 
they have no idea what theyre getting they think its an 
apple pie in red cellophane said jennifer sanders president of 
cowpies recently founded in this san francisco bayarea city 
sanders and her two partners gayle massey a san francisco 
advertiser and santa monica businessman donald grant actually 
scour the fields for the real thing 
so far theyve filled about 100 orders many are for birthday 
parties but nearly half of the pies carry a more pointed message 
one homeowner ordered a pie for a carpenter whose work he didnt 
like another sent a bovine confection to his bank 
more popular are orders from employees seeking a memorable gift 
for a boss or coworker 
its strictly anonymous unless they specify otherwise 
