expected to be raised when mrs aquino visits the united states in 
november 
any new bases agreement must be ratified by twothirds of the 
23member philippine senate last month 12 senators called for the 
bases to be closed in 1991 that would be enough to block any 
extension of the agreement 
mrs aquino also refused to say whether she personally believes a 
new agreement would be in the national interest 
i dont think this is the time to be defining it because we 
dont know first of all do the americans still want to use these 
facilities she said 
and secondly what are they wanting in the matter of the use of 
these bases and also what are they prepared to do this has to be 
discussed lengthily if and when we start talks on the bases 
regardless of the outcome mrs aquino said she wanted to retain 
close ties with the united states the philippines former colonial 
ruler 
i am hoping that both the americans and the filipinos can 
maintain a very friendly relationship because we filipinos would 
like to believe that there is more to the relationship than just 
the matter of the bases she said 
i think sometimes some of us believe that maybe where some 
americans are concerned the only thing that probably ties the two 
nations together is the presence of the us facilities in our 
bases 
