bushs proposal in the spring for wholesale reductions in nato and 
warsaw pact troops and nonnuclear armories in europe 
some 20 nations are believed to either possess chemical weapons 
or the capability to manufacture them the danger they might be used 
is considered by many analysts to at least equal the threat of 
nuclear war 
one of the main worries is that chemical weapons smaller even 
than a pack of cigarettes could be concealed by a terrorist and used 
for political extortion or set off in a violent rampage 
describing verification of chemical weapons as even more 
difficult than keeping track of nuclear arms an official said 
many of these weapons are small and can be produced in a small 
room but the agreement would help us along the path to a treaty 
also on baker and shevardnadzes agenda is preparing for 
president bushs first summit meeting with soviet president mikhail 
s gorbachev 
the two superpowers in 1987 signed an unprecedented treaty to 
eliminate all their intermediaterange nuclear missiles it featured 
the firstever program for reciprocal inspection of bases where the 
missiles are deployed as well as manufacturing plants 
it apparently has worked without a hitch and set the two sides on 
a path for cooperating on the chemical weapons treaty 
