we return in the spirit of peace love and national 
reconciliation nujoma told a news conference at his new home in 
katatura the black township on the outskirts of windhoek 
no words may express my happiness at joining my family friends 
and comrades he said the years spent abroad have at times been 
characterized by loneliness at other times there was great 
happiness when we achieved successes we never lost sight of our 
principal objective freedom and independence for namibia 
the 60yearold nationalist kissed the tarmac at windhoeks 
airport embraced swapo colleagues and his 89yearold mother 
thousands of cheering supporters kept out of the terminal by 
police gathered at the airport gates to greet nujoma who reached 
out of the car wavingand shaking hands most wore the red blue and 
green colors of the independence movement 
black trade unions urged their members to skip work in order to 
join in welcoming nujoma who arrived aboard an ethiopian airlines 
jet after a flight from luanda angola 
trucks and buses loaded with cheering supporters waving banners 
and raising clenched fists followed the car through windhoek to 
katatura people on the street joined in the cheers while others 
jeered and raised their fists in obscene gestures as the motorcade 
passed 
earlier today police announced the arrest of a suspect in the 
assassination of lubowski police inspector kierie du rand said the 
suspect was a 50yearold white man with an irish passport arrested 
in windhoek on wednesday he reportedly came to namibia from cape 
town south africa 
his name was not released and du rand said additional arrests 
were expected the south african press association said police were 
investigating a possible link with the irish republican army but 
did not elaborate 
lubowski 37 was killed by automatic rifle fire outside his 
windhoek home tuesday night a civil rights lawyer he was a member 
of swapos election directorate and helped direct its campaign for 
unsupervised elections scheduled for early november as a prelude 
to independence next year 
swapo said the assassination of lubowski was intended to create 
instability prior to the elections which swapo is widely favored to 
dominate and to frighten whites at a time when racial unity is 
growing 
asked about fears for his own security nujoma said whenever i 
move about i am concerned about my own safety all swapo leaders 
have unarmed bodyguards and say they have received no answer to 
their request to form a registered security company they said they 
have applied for police protection but they want un forces to 
monitor the police guards 
south africa which has ruled namibia 74 years has agreed to 
independence for the territory under un supervision as part of a 
regional peace accord also calling for withdrawal of cuban troops 
from angola 
on wednesday posters appeared in windhoek with a photograph of 
nujoma and a target superimposed on his face 
a local newspaper editor gwen lister said she received two 
phone calls wednesday from men saying they belonged to the white 
wolves and that the white supremacist organization killed lubowski 
men identifying themselves as whites wolves have carried out 
several attacks on blacks and antiapartheid activists in south 
africa police say they have not been able to prove the organization 
exists 
fighting between swapo guerrillas and the south africanled 
security forces ended in april since then there have been only 
isolated violent incidents in this territory whose 13 million 
population is 84 percent black with the rest nearly equal parts 
white and mixedrace people 
lubowski died only hours after namibias nine largest political 
parties including swapo signed a code of conduct for the elections 
that prohibits violence he was widely known abroad and his killing 
was condemned by the united states britain west germany norway 
sweden amd zambia among others 
nujoma is not considered a rigid ideologue although his 
organization is leftistleaning and favors a socialist economy he 
is viewed as a shrewd instinctive politician maintaining the 
presidency of swapo since 1960 despite occasional challenges 
under his leadership the movement was recognized by the united 
nations as the sole and authentic representative of the namibian 
people although the territory had dozens of political parties 
the united nations dropped that designation before its contingent 
came to namibia this year to monitor the independence process 
</TEXT>
