an unannounced highlevel contact between us 
and nicaraguan officials last weekend is not a prelude to a 
resumption of direct dialogue between the two countries according 
to state department officials 
the weekend meeting in managua the first such contact between 
the two countries in almost five years involved president daniel 
ortega and a us delegation consisting of members of congress and 
