among those vacancies that we dont have a candidate in process yet 
is to be the deputy commissioner of patents and the deputy 
commissioner of trademarks said untermeyer 
the federal grain inspector is also one of those positions 
many of these jobs make me wonder why they are presidential 
appointments at all but the congress has decreed that they should 
be presidential appointments so they are he said 
elsewhere we have 88 percent of the positions that count 
either on the job or awaiting confirmation he said 
the democratic study group in a blistering report released aug 
29 charged that 160 of 394 senior positions more than 40 percent 
had been left vacant by bush as of early august it said it 
appeared a significant portion of the government is on automatic 
pilot 
the democratic study group said the vacancies include five 
assistant secretaries of education a deputy attorney general and 
an undersecretary of state as well as the commerce post 
the white house has complained that its nominees were facing 
slowgoing in the democraticcontrolled senate 
senate majority leader george mitchell of maine last week said 
bush had no grounds to complain because he has failed to make 
nominations for nearly half of the fulltime positions in executive 
departments and independent agencies which require senate 
confirmation 
untermeyer said there is always about a 12 percent at the top 
of the executive branch as people resign retire move on or out of 
their office for other reasons 
i describe my job as rather like painting the golden gate 
bridge once you finish it you have to start in at the other end 
and start painting it again said untermeyer 
he scoffed at the impression left by the critics that the bush 
administration is somehow still in the starting blocks that it 
was gulliver tied down by strings of red tapes this is not true 
this administration has been enormously even historically 
successful in establishing itself and when faced with a congress 
that is in the hands of the opposition it is most impressive the 
bush assistant said 
the 73rd female presidential appointee was margaret machol who 
bush said he will nominate to be a commissioner of the commodity 
futures trading corporation 
