<TEXT>
nuclear reactor manufacturer babcock amp wilcox 
co said thursday it is adding framatome sa of france as a partner 
in its nuclear services business and is considering a broader 
partnership to develop new commercial reactors 
charles w pryor jr general manager of babcock amp wilcoxs 
existing nuclear services business said adding framatome will help 
babcock amp wilcox broaden its scope in an industry that both 
companies believe is nearing a comeback in the united states 
no new nuclear plants have been ordered in the united states 
since 1978 
framatome built and services all 55 pressurized water reactors 
operating in france 
pryor said the venture to be called bampw nuclear services co 
based at lynchburg va will be staffed by the existing 750 
employees of babcock amp wilcoxs services company and will be managed 
by babcock amp wilcox 
the deal takes effect nov 1 
jean claude leny chairman of framatome said his company is 
paying 50 million for its interest in the venture and that 
operating costs would be shared equally by the parent companies 
the 1 billionayear us nuclear services market targeted by 
babcock amp wilcox includes refueling inspection and repair of plant 
components maintenance licensing and engineering support and plant 
management services 
pryor said babcock amp wilcox also is exploring the possibility of 
an alliance with nuclear power international a european group 
including framatome and siemens of west germany to develop a new 
reactor design for the us market 
babcock amp wilcox is a unit of mcdermott international inc a new 
orleansbased energy concern 
</TEXT>
