thursday was the second day in office for the ministers of the 
new solidaritycontrolled government 
prime minister tadeusz mazowiecki a solidarity newspaper editor 
until he took on his historic mission aug 24 held only one 
publicly reported meeting thursday it was a session with austrian 
vicechancellor josef riegler 
mazowiecki who had been an adviser to walesa is leading the 
east blocs first noncommunist government since the communists 
consolidated power after world war ii 
many of the new governments plans to introduce westernstyle 
economic reform to combat tripledigit inflation its 39 billion 
foreign debt and other economic ills are likely to further undermine 
a lagging standard of living mazowiecki has said 
the new political leadership has declared that the sacrifices 
will be needed for longterm gains but they are clearly worried 
about public patience and support 
no details were offered on the trip suggested by walesa 
on two previous occasions this year he has used his tremendous 
personal influence with poles 
he traveled around poland to urge workers not to strike while 
talks were under way last spring that resulted in the 
relegalization of his labor movement 
he also made stops around the country to advocate support for 
solidarity campaigns during the unprecedented democratic 
parliamentary elections in june solidarity won a sweeping victory 
and then successfully bargained to lead the government 
in his comments thursday walesa also looked ahead saying 
political divisions between solidarity and the communist party are 
now following a new confrontational model not by means of 
force but a peaceful confrontation 
after pluralisms victory there will not be a need for a 
confrontational structure he said predicting the advent of other 
political parties and other trade unions 
the official pap news agency reported thursday that communist 
