<TEXT>
personal bankruptcy filings have doubled 
since 1980 and account for one half the annual fees paid by bank 
credit card holders said the president of visa usa in announcing 
a nationwide crackdown on fraudulent filers 
jon cristoffersen said wednesday that efforts are under way in 
los angeles dallas houston and chicago and will reach most major 
areas by year end 
bankruptcy can be an appropriate way for honest people to deal 
with a financial problem he said but our concern is with the 
fraudulent filing which can be as many as one in three 
personal bankruptcy filings have increased since 1980 to about 
600000 last year or one in 178 households cristoffersen said that 
socked the bank card industry with total losses of 15 billion in 
1988 as bankrupt cardholders simply wrote off their credit card debt 
about half of everyones annual fees for bank cards comes from 
bankruptcy he said if were able to deal with even 20 to 30 
percent of the fraud the payback to the public will be 
substantial 
most people who file for bankruptcy fraudulently have been able 
to get away with it cristoffersen said because twothirds of the 
banks with assets over 1 billion havent been challenging them 
visas new program encourages member banks to screen for fraud 
and abuse of the federal bankruptcy law challenge filings in court 
and seek criminal prosecution 
bankruptcy frauds include those who dont declare all their 
assets such as real estate in other states or inheritances they 
also include those who sell assets below their true market value or 
transfer ownership to a third party or relative abusers also 
include those who have the ability to pay back their debts but 
choose not to 
the stories are legend like the man who wanted to spread out 
payments for his jaguar or the chap who lost 350000 on a single 
roll of the dice after he took out 30 bank cards cristoffersen 
said 
cristoffersen speaking at a convention of the national 
foundation for consumer credit inc outlined a tough program that 
so far has enlisted 70 member banks those banks including 
citibank bank of america and chase manhattan issue 60 percent of 
visas 118 million cards in the country and are victims of 75 
percent of all bankruptcies 
when member banks in the program receive bankruptcy notices they 
will immediately review the account and if they suspect fraud or 
abuse notify all other members listed on the bankruptcy petition 
the other members will do a similar search and when two or more 
believe they have found fraud or abuse they will collectively use a 
single local law firm to represent them 
by multiple members reviewing bankruptcies they can put 
together a clearer picture of fraud and abuse and make it 
economically feasible to go after the abusers said kenneth r 
crone who heads the bankruptcy recovery program for visa 
the program also includes pursuit of criminal prosecution visa 
has hired a former fbi agent who will investigate cases prepare 
them for review by the fbi and seek prosecution by the us attorney 
on a fasttrack basis under a special arrangement with the justice 
department 
in los angeles the number of accounts showing up with fraud or 
abuse that are being challenged under the pilot program has doubled 
to more than 300 in the past three months crone said 
that represents a small percentage of the more than 30000 
fraudulent or abusive bankruptcies among the 51000 declared each 
year in los angeles but crone believes the program is sending the 
message that theres a darn good chance theyll get caught that 
the bankruptcy petition will be thrown out of court and theyll have 
to pay attorney fees and face criminal prosecution 
the bankruptcy reform act which was rewritten in 1978 was 
designed to encourage chapter 11 or chapter 13 personal 
reorganization filings wherein the debtor pays back creditors 
as much as possible over three to five years crone said 
but weve seen an incredible boom of chapter 7 bankruptcies 
where there are no assets and people get their entire unsecured debt 
discharged crone said credit cards are unsecured so theyre 
the first to get written off 
of the nearly 600000 personal bankruptcy filings in 1988 about 
95 percent were chapter 7 filings visa said 
the national foundation for consumer credit is the parent 
organization for more than 400 consumer credit counseling offices 
and offers free counseling services 
visa the worlds largest consumer payment system has more than 
19000 us bank members with 120 billion in payment volume a year 
