supply problems expired incentives and patient 
consumers combined to torpedo early september sales of two 
japanbased companies us plants and drop car and truck sales 06 
percent the companies say 
the eight major us automakers on wednesday reported that their 
vehicle sales for sept 110 dropped to an average daily rate of 
30333 this year compared with a rate of 30522 during the same 
time last year 
pulling down the yeartoyear comparison were sluggish car sales 
by honda motor co and car and light truck sales by nissan motor 
corp 
sales of civics and accords made at hondas marysville ohio 
plant sold at a rate 36 percent below last years during the period 
and nissan pickup truck and sentra car sales fell 721 percent and 
791 percent respectively 
honda spokesman jeff leestma said few civics were available 
during the period because of a model changeover at the factory he 
also speculated consumers may be waiting to see the redesigned 1990 
honda accord 
